ld\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s synchronized 3-meter springboard\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China also took the bronze for the Women's 4x100m Free Relay with swimmers Yufei Zhang, Yujie Cheng, Qingfeng Wu and Yiting Yu.\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9928969626493864, \"rank\": 0.006611745025222234, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bronze\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers Yufei Zhang\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"Yujie Cheng\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"Qingfeng Wu\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"Yiting Yu\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Auriane Mallo-Breton led 8-3 against Kong Man Wai Vivian in the Women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Fencing final until Kong made an epic comeback, tying 12-12 as time expired, then winning with a sudden-death hit.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Auriane Mallo-Breton\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"Kong Man\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"Wai Vivian\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 633}, {\"ngram\": \"Kong\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"an epic comeback\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"a sudden-death hit\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kong is the first woman from Hong Kong, China to win an Olympic fencing gold and the first from her National Olympic Committee to win gold since 1996.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9989581